- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is likely because the paper develops an algorithm to decide whether a HDA can be sculpted, and also discusses the combinatorial structure of sculptures.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is likely because the paper deals with modeling concurrent behavior, which is a common topic in programming language research.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is likely because the paper involves combinatorial and geometric models for concurrency, which are often studied in discrete mathematics.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible because the paper discusses the complexity of deciding whether a HDA can be sculpted.
